  <summary>1/6/1987--Introduced.
Requires any State receiving Federal funds for acquired immune deficiency syndrome (AIDS) counseling and education to: (1) have a system to trace the partners of individuals with AIDS; (2) test those individuals for AIDS; and (3) counsel those individuals about the infectious nature of the syndrome.</summary>
